          "ruleId": "variableScope",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "The scope of the variable 'opcode' can be reduced. Warning: Be careful when fixing this message, especially when there are inner loops. Here is an example where cppcheck will write that the scope for 'i' can be reduced:\\012void f(int x)\\012{\\012    int i = 0;\\012    if (x) {\\012        // it's safe to move 'int i = 0;' here\\012        for (int n = 0; n < 10; ++n) {\\012            // it is possible but not safe to move 'int i = 0;' here\\012            do_something(&i);\\012        }\\012    }\\012}\\012When you see this message it is always safe to reduce the variable scope 1 level."
          },
